Function Reference/username exists « WordPress Codex
-----------

Returns the user ID if the user exists or `null` if the user doesn't
exist.

Usage
-----

` <?php username_exists( $username ); ?> `

Parameters
----------

 `$username` 
:   ([*string*](/How_to_Pass_Tag_Parameters#String "How to Pass Tag Parameters"))
    (*required*) a string representing the username to check for
    existence.
    Default: *None*

Return Values
-------------

 (mixed) 
:   This function returns the user ID if the user exists or `null` if
    the user does not exist.

Examples
--------

Use `username_exists()` in your scripts to decide whether the given
username exists.

    <?php  
           $username = $_POST['username'];
           if ( username_exists( $username ) )
               echo "Username In Use!";
           else
               echo "Username Not In Use!";
    ?>

Notes
-----

Change Log
----------

Source File
-----------

`username_exists()` is located in `wp-includes/user.php`.

